public class EventParameterProxy
extends ParameterProxy

An event parameter for a Waters module.

An event parameter is a parameter that is bound to an event or set of events when a module is compiled. An event parameter behaves like an event declaration (EventDeclProxy), in that it introduces an event or event array that can be used in the module's components. The only difference is that the events do not come from their module itself, but from another module from which their module is instantiated.

The documentation of class ModuleProxy contains an example demonstrating the use of event parameters.

Author:
Robi Malik
